-- Rothschild Chairman to Lead Barclays External Review, Sky Says
-- B y   S o f i a   H o r t a   e   C o s t a
-- 2012-07-22T15:17:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-22/rothschild-chairman-to-lead-barclays-external-review-sky-says.html
Anthony Salz, executive vice-
chairman of investment bank Rothschild, will lead the
independent inquiry into  Barclays Plc (BARC) ’s culture and practices,
 Sky News  reported, citing people it didn’t identify.  Barclays Deputy Chairman Sir Michael Rake will supervise
the inquiry, which is to establish a new code of conduct for
U.K. banks, Sky News said. Barclays will announce details of the
inquiry tomorrow, according to the broadcaster.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sofia Horta e Costa in London at 
 shortaecosta@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
